<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
      <h1 class="white">General FAQ</h1>
      <div class="faq">
        <%= link_to "Open All", "#", class: 'btn btn-primary openall' %> <%= link_to "Close All", "#", class: 'btn btn-primary closeall' %>
      </div>
      
      <div class="panel-group" id="accordion" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true">
        <div class="panel panel-default">
          <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingOne">
            <h4 class="panel-title">
              <a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
                How do I add a book?
              </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse in" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingOne">
            <div class="panel-body">
              <ol>
                <li>Please sign in or sign up for free now</li>
                <li>In the Search bar, search for a book, and then click on Submit</li>
                <li>Under the Book cover, click Add Book.</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr />
        <h1 class="white">Error Messages</h1>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
          <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingTwo">
            <h4 class="panel-title">
              <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                Error! Book has not been added. Book duplicate?
              </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingTwo">
            <div class="panel-body">
              <ol>
                <li>Check to make sure the book you are trying to add as not already been added.</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
          <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingSix">
            <h4 class="panel-title">
              <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseSix" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                Error! Did not return any search results.
              </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseSix" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingSix">
            <div class="panel-body">
              <ol>
                <li>Check to make sure the name of the book you're trying to find isn't misspelled.</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
          <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingSeven">
            <h4 class="panel-title">
              <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseSeven" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                Error! The book does not belong to you!
              </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseSeven" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingSeven">
            <div class="panel-body">
              <ol>
                <li>Check to make sure the book that you are trying to edit or delete is a book that you have added. This error message occurs whenever you trying to edit or delete a book that belong to you.</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
          <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingEight">
            <h4 class="panel-title">
              <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseEight" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                Error! No books have been added.
              </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseEight" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingEight">
            <div class="panel-body">
              <ol>
                <li>There have been no books added. Consider signing in or signing in to add your own books.</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr />
        <h1 class="white">Website FAQ</h1>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
          <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingThree">
            <h4 class="panel-title">
              <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                Specifics of this website.
              </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingThree">
            <div class="panel-body">
              <ol>
              	<li><%= link_to "Bootstrap-Sass 3.3.6", "https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap-sass", target: '_blank' %></li>
              	<li><%= link_to "Devise 4.0.1", "https://github.com/plataformatec/devise", target: '_blank' %></li>
              	<li><%= link_to "Font-Awesome-Rails 4.6.2.0", "https://github.com/FortAwesome/Font-Awesome", target: '_blank' %></li>
              	<li><%= link_to "Git 2.7.3", "https://git-scm.com/", target: '_blank' %></li>
              	<li><%= link_to "Googlebooks 0.0.9", "https://github.com/zeantsoi/GoogleBooks", target: '_blank' %></li>
              	<li><%= link_to "Paperclip 4.3.6", "https://github.com/thoughtbot/paperclip", target: '_blank' %></li>
              	<li><%= link_to "Rails 4.2.5.2", "https://github.com/rails/rails", target: '_blank' %></li>
              	<li><%= link_to "Readmorejs-Rails 0.0.12", "https://github.com/seankay/readmorejs-rails", target: '_blank' %></li>
              	<li><%= link_to "Ruby 2.3.0p0", "https://github.com/ruby/ruby", target: '_blank' %></li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
          <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingFour">
            <h4 class="panel-title">
              <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour">
                What is the purpose of this website?
              </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingFour">
            <div class="panel-body">
              <ol>
              	<li>The purpose of this website is further develop my skills as a Ruby on Rails developer and to showcase written code.</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
          <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="headingFive">
            <h4 class="panel-title">
              <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFive" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                What are the future developments of this website?
              </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseFive" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingFive">
            <div class="panel-body">
              <ol>
                <li>For the Authors page:</li>
                  <ol type="a">
                    <li>To have only one author per line.</li>
                    <li>To make the names clickable so that once clicked, will redirect to the author's page where it will display all the books that have been added by that particular author.</li>
                  </ol>
                <li>For the Categories page:</li>
                  <ol type="a">
      	            <li>To make the categories clickable so that once clicked, will redirect to a page where it displays all books that have the same category.</li>
                  </ol>
                <li>For the Search page:</li>
                  <ol type="a">
                    <li>The ability to add multiple books at the same time</li>
                    <li>A filter including, but not limited to:</li>
                      <ol type="i">
                        <li>Category</li>
                        <li>Author</li>
                        <li>Date</li>
                        <li>Ratings</li>
                        <li>Number of pages</li>
                      </ol>
                    <li>More book results with pagination</li>
                  </ol>
                  <li>A profile page for each user.</li>
                  <ol type="a">
                    <li>A page showing all books a user has added.</li>
                    <li>Either select one or all of the users books to delete.</li>
                    <li>Personal statistics on the user, including, but not limited to:
                    <ol type="i">
                      <li>When the user joined</li>
                      <li>How many books they have added</li>
                      <li>How many total reviews they have added</li>
                    </ol>
                  </ol>
                <li>A filter to show books who do and do not have a review</li>
                <li>An advanced search function, including, but not limited to:</li>
                  <ol type="a">
                    <li>Only show free ebooks</li>
                    <li>Only show paid ebooks</li>
                    <li>Only show books that are downloadable</li>
                  </ol>
                <li>When a user who is not logged in and tries to add a book it redirects to the homepage without adding the book. Fix it to where it adds the book whenever they sign in or create an account</li>
                <li>A working "Reset Password" link</li>
                <li>A contact form to send improvements or bugs</li>
                <li>A confirmation page to make sure email during registration is a working email</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div><!-- End Accordion -->
      
    </div>
  <div>
</div>
<script>
$('.closeall').click(function(){
  $('.panel-collapse.in')
    .collapse('hide');
});
$('.openall').click(function(){
  $('.panel-collapse:not(".in")')
    .collapse('show');
});
</script>